question: 対比
sourceMnemonic: When you look at something <kanji>versus</kanji> something else, you <kanji>compare</kanji> them with one another. You look at the <vocabulary>contrast</vocabulary> between them and make a <vocabulary>comparison</vocabulary>.
sourceReadingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well.
